reviews.review: Hugely entertaining, amazing action and visuals and the acting was top notch from everyone. Great to finally see Rey, Poe and Finn come together! Yes, there are a few plot points that might annoy die-hard fans, but if you want big blockbuster entertainment, you can't get a better send-off! The light sabre sequence on the Death Star was awe-inspiring!
It's far from perfect and nearly undoes The Last Jedi but since The Last Jedi was the worst Star Wars movie ever made that's not the worst thing.

this movie felt like what jj did with millenium falcon in the force awakens except moments like that happen like 10 times trought the entire movie and back to back nearing the end of the movie to the point you just dont give a shit, a constant "hey do you remember (thing you liked from the originalk trilogy)" also why did rey need finn, poe and everyone else, if anything everyone needs rey, the moment shes not on screen with the rest of the cast the rest gets fucked up and beaten up bad, literally there's nothing poe and finn do that rey cant already, they are just there to be carried by rey and ocassionally "save her" from situations the she could've handled on her own as well of a whole bunch of bullshit but going into those would be going into spoiler territory so i wont talk about those, the only good thing in this movie i can think of was carrie fisher and sadly she's fucking dead

And the final trilogy goes out with a safe, corporate-pleasing whimper.   Spent an hour and a half hunting Macguffins before getting to the meat of the movie.   There are a couple of scenes that conjure up the magic of the original trilogy, but they are buried in an otherwise joyless endeavor where the stakes seem impossibly low (despite the universe being at stake, ostensibly).  Add to that a washed out color palette and embarrassingly uninspired visual effects and you've got, well, I guess what we've come to expect from Disney.   At least Solo was fun.
